Think of life as an infinite ocean—mysterious, deep, and limitless. We see its shores bustling with activity, yet the far side remains unknown. Those who ventured to uncover its secrets never returned. Life is full of colors and vibrance, yet solitude and silence coexist within it.

Life is eternal—before creation, it existed in the Creator's will. After its completion, it will return to Him. Life consumes time, swallows centuries, and in a fleeting moment, it can ignite revolutions. It’s both fragile and resilient, fleeting and eternal.

