Life gives and receives, connects and separates. It’s above triumph and loss, beyond gain and deprivation. It’s ancient and modern, forever evolving, yet eternally constant.

In the end, life is a message—a flowing river carrying the wisdom of mountains to the depths of the ocean. It reminds us to respect its essence, for life is a reflection of the Creator's infinite brilliance.

